    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Planes with two blades which are used to cut a tongue. One of the blades may be covered so that the remaining blade cuts a groove into which the tongue will fit.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000000/VP</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000005711/Blackburn, Illustrated Encyclopedia of Woodworking Handtools (1974)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Stel van twee schaven, de groef- en de messingschaaf, waarmee de groef en de messing geschaafd worden voor de verbinding van planken.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Dutch</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000205/AAT-Ned</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000113770/AAT-Ned (1994-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000052490/Clason, Elsevier tools and ironware (1982)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000079049/Haslinghuis, bouwkundige termen (1997)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000095117/Haslinghuis, Bouwkundige termen (1997)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Hobel mit zwei Hobeleisen, die zum Schneiden einer Feder verwendet werden. Eines der Hobeleisen kann bedeckt werden, so dass das verbliebene Hobeleisen eine Nut schneidet, in welche die Feder passen wird.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>German</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000232/IfM-SMB-PK</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000122134/IfM Berlin</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>具有雙刀片的鉋具，可用來切割出榫舌。刀片之一可能受到覆蓋，而使剩下的刀片可刮出溝槽，令榫舌嵌入。</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Chinese (traditional)</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000250/AS-Academia Sinica</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
